Crypt-OpenSSL-ECDSA version 0.03s
================================

This module provides an interface to the ECDSA (Elliptic Curve Digital
Signature Algorithm) functions in OpenSSL.


INSTALLATION

To compile and install this module type the following:

   perl Makefile.PL
   make
   make test
   make install

By default, this will compile against and link with OpenSSL in
/usr/include/openssl and /usr/lib/libcrypto.so

You can change the location of the OpenSSL headers and library to use with the
OPENSSL_PREFIX (which defaults to /usr)
environment variable, for example:

OPENSSL_PREFIX=/home/mikem/playpen/openssl-1.0.2/ perl Makefile.PL


DEPENDENCIES

This module requires these other modules and libraries:

 Crypt::OpenSSL::Bignum
 Crypt::OpenSSL::EC
 OpenSSL (0.9.8a or later) libcrypto.so library and headers with EC and ECDSA enabled

